Comment: 0,0:22:10.29,0:22:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{ED START}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.97,0:22:21.72,Default,ed,0,0,0,,There is one song I cannot ever forget
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.72,0:22:27.35,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Still, there's a face I'm willing to forget
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.35,0:22:30.31,Default,ed,0,0,0,,With her feelings messed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.31,0:22:33.19,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Alice got completely lost
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.19,0:22:38.38,Default,ed,0,0,0,,The midst of summer \NBrought her into one tricky love maze
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.70,0:22:45.29,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I want you to hug tightly\NAnd never let go of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.29,0:22:50.67,Default,ed,0,0,0,,One scared and timid tiny girl
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.67,0:22:57.55,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I quite remember our very first kiss \NAnd the beginning of all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.13,0:23:03.97,Default,ed,0,0,0,,While birds were singing for us...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.04,0:23:13.16,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I'll take a car and take a lonely trip
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.16,0:23:18.36,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I know it'll bring me \NTo the seashore
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.36,0:23:21.41,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Where only the the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.41,0:23:24.45,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Dazzlingly bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.45,0:23:29.98,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Could witness my long-awaited happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.99,0:01:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, it's round two. \NMy opponent is the Spaniard Marchesa Broir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.99,0:02:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure, Jin, \NI have to defeat her, by all means.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.47,0:02:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, no later than in the next, third round, \NI will play with Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.97,0:02:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, if I keep winning and winning, \NI will make it to the finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.47,0:02:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, do you believe \NI'll have a chance to play with Hiromi too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.46,0:02:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, Hiromi's block is the most difficult one,\Nso to make it happen, she must also keep winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.45,0:02:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Odd to see you here, Ranko.\NYou're a day before his death anniversary.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.96,0:02:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because I have a match tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.67,0:02:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, against Broir, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.24,0:02:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.95,0:02:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your senses keen. \NThe opponent is the world rankings' fourteenth after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.78,0:02:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Your accustomed way of dealing with obstacles \Nis using the power to break through. But it has a fatal flaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.02,0:02:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Only if you learn to wait for your chance, \Nyou'll be victorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.24,0:02:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a 14-year-old brat.\NI'll get her single-handed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.90,0:02:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If we were to beat her off court,\NI might've said the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.35,0:02:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand your confidence, \Nbut you should also be so kind as to acknowledge reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.36,0:02:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I win?\NWhat if I still win?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.86,0:03:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then wish whatever you want, \Nand I'll grant it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.86,0:03:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.41,0:03:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I'll wish to see Jin?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.82,0:03:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Silly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.07,0:03:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.87,0:03:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,See him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.61,0:03:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you win all of the tennis matches, \Nit won't bring home a late person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.22,0:03:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Be it so, I would've been on the court myself now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.72,0:03:36.75,Default,,0,0,80,,{\bord4\blur15\3c&HAC907F&\t(0,600,\bord0\blur0.55)\c&HFEFEFD&\fnGabriola\fs48\frz359.6\3a&H2D&\fscx184\fscy146}Episode 10       \h\N\N\N\NChallenger,                             \h \N\h                            Ranko!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.07,0:03:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What Hiromi and Coach Katsura are trying to pull, \Nwhat they are trying to achieve, I understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.02,0:04:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Countless famous players tried it, \Nultimately declaring such a play impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.04,0:04:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika, you are questioning your own tennis now.\NTherefore I have to warn you in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.03,0:04:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite being theoretically possible, chances of such a play \Nbeing practically successful on a real court are extremely low.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.31,0:04:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Still in the first round Hiromi have \Nsuccessfully defeated Morita, a pro, with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.23,0:04:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika... For the first time in years \NI miss the sounds of Chopin's Mazurka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.67,0:04:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Her posture is lower than anyone's.\NShe steps into the ball further than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When receiving the bouncing ball, \Nshe hits it lower than anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.68,0:04:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And when a ball hit so low is being returned,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.73,0:04:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the opponent is never in the position for receiving. \NAs a result, the return ace is almost guaranteed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.19,0:04:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everyone is capable of such a play.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.81,0:04:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how Katsura described it:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.60,0:04:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"Engendering this style of play in Oka \Nwas Munakata's plan ever since he was teaching her himself."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.82,0:04:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, he never managed to see \Nhow this idea is being embodied in Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.06,0:05:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This was his wager for future, \Nthat's why their trainings were always that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.83,0:05:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,By just looking at her, you'll never get it with your head. \NAnd surely won't be able to repeat her play.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.59,0:05:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi managed to do it, because it's her. \NIs that what you want to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.83,0:05:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, Munakata, and finally Katsura Daigo \Ndid it together. This is what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.80,0:05:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, for real?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.82,0:05:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Living in a hotel starting tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.89,0:05:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The venue is far. Most of the participants \Nindwell the same hotel. Packed like sardines!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.75,0:05:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid... \NBy any chance, may I come with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.32,0:05:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I once played local \N"Space Battle" arcade there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.83,0:05:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No offence, but I'll have matters \Nof life and death on my mind you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.84,0:05:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it easy, Hiromi.\NSecond round is a piece of cake for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.76,0:05:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To think of it, with such a first round,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.38,0:05:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,even the gold medal is no longer a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.86,0:05:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you win, shall we go together?\NPlay "Space Battle." I'm looking forward to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.09,0:06:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.66,0:06:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, Hiromi, \Nyou'll show a great match, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.20,0:06:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get ahead of yourself. Even winning round 3 \Nwill be a great luck. I aim to get into the best 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.26,0:06:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No, still, something was different the last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.87,0:06:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Burning her fire both for love and for tennis, \NOka Hiromi is being torn apa-pa-pa-pa-part!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.20,0:06:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You jester!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.16,0:06:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna eat some ice cream?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.44,0:06:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.82,0:06:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It may sound banal, \Nbut I'll be waiting for you in the round 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.17,0:06:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It may sound banal, \Nbut some rankings' #14 is not a threat for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.59,0:06:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!  \NAttagirl!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.14,0:06:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll be back in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.17,0:06:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the fifth match of the second round, \Nand the first Marchesa Broir's appearance!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.93,0:06:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,#14 in world rankings,\Nfourteen-year-old court fairy she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:07:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is her first time to play \Nin front of Japan's tennis fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.22,0:07:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Her opponent - having her right wrist injury overcame, \Nmade a dazzling comeback as a southpaw, Midorikawa Ranko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.49,0:07:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She spectacularly won the first round,\Nso in the second round we expect nothing less from her!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.05,0:07:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Service: Midorikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.61,0:07:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.79,0:07:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,0-15.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.20,0:07:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Todo...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.74,0:08:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The match played by Midorikawa that day \Nwas somewhat out of this world.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.71,0:08:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was so extraordinary, my whole next letter \Ndeserves to be dedicated to this match only.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.11,0:08:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's about how deeply astonished \NI was with this match.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.19,0:08:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Queen's Cup.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.22,0:08:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The fifth match of the second round.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.57,0:08:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Midorikawa's play that day,\Ndespite all the countless worthy matches I've seen before,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.83,0:08:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}has moved me to the core.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was truly a life-and-death battle \Nwith all that competitive spirit in Midorikawa's play.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.68,0:08:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can hardly describe everything that I saw there.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.43,0:08:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At first, Broir was dominating the match, \Nsetting her own pace. Forehand,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.40,0:08:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}backhand, serve... Whichever she hit, \Nher perfect shots were always reaching Midorikawa's court.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.95,0:08:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Midorikawa was helpless \Nas if though she was idling.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.40,0:08:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Over time, her impotent exhaustion became apparent. \NI was not only seeing it, I even felt it myself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.35,0:09:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Prodigy Broir in all her glory!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.04,0:09:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Power hitter Midorikawa \Nis all out of chances to keep up with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.97,0:09:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we can see the Broir's famous coaching staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.52,0:09:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,10 people in total. It's not only the play that they supervise. \NA doctor and a lawyer also always accompany her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.17,0:09:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, an additional standby team is in the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.52,0:09:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Considerable, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.94,0:09:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it's player Ryder! \NWith Broir, she shares the favourite's status.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.97,0:09:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean Ryder is bound to take on her rival Broir here \Nto settle the scores!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.20,0:09:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,15-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.63,0:09:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,30-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.36,0:09:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}First set, sixth game.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.77,0:09:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Midorikawa never managed \Nto break Broir's service-game. Ultimately...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.87,0:09:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She was defeated 6-0.\NLost the first set scoreless.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.32,0:09:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And then... \NThe second set has started with issue far graver.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.75,0:10:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here I am, Jin. Looks like until now \NI was struggling in vain anyway. I should give it a try.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.66,0:10:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm a little scared, \Nbut I still think I have a good chance to success.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.66,0:10:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is it alright? \NWell then...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.63,0:10:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's settled.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.64,0:10:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you an idiot, Ranko?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.28,0:10:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Todo...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.57,0:10:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Todo, Midorikawa was playing with her right again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.52,0:11:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Although doctors prohibited even holding the racket \Nwith her right, leave alone playing tennis!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.83,0:11:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For the first time in life \NI saw someone playing tennis so freely and happily.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.03,0:11:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Her eyes... \NWere literally glowing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.99,0:11:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She really is idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.31,0:11:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Tries to compensate her inferiority \Nholding the racket her usual way,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.94,0:11:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,making all the effort \Nof healing her right hand go to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.92,0:11:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the actual Ranko's right hand's comeback. \NHer eternal dream fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.87,0:11:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why couldn't you just wait? \NOnly six months left... Year at most!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.84,0:11:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This match she has to win, for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.76,0:11:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If she does not win this match,\Nshe'll never be able to play with Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.85,0:11:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,, Don't talk nonsense.\NIt's not about Ochou.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.54,0:11:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,For a year already Ranko's only target...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.37,0:11:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.52,0:12:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the second set, \NMidorikawa gave Broir a run for her money!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.53,0:12:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the second set Midorikawa is holding the racket \Nwith her right, which pays off!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.53,0:12:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Rankings' #14 Broir \Nis fighting her as equal now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.47,0:12:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Although this way she is playing \Non a right-handed player level again,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.05,0:12:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,being as reasonable as much reason it demands, \NI'm still a little worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.69,0:12:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Care to explain?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.47,0:12:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She was forbidden to play \Nbecause her right hand injury was a serious one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.92,0:12:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,15-40.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.92,0:12:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in the second set Midorikawa \Nhas reached the set point already!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.04,0:13:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In the first set she was swept away with zero to six, \Nbut her regained power has turned the tables!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.93,0:13:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it...\NIt's a little numb already.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.43,0:13:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a matter of one point now. \NTodo...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.94,0:13:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one point now stands between Midorikawa \Nand the final set, which she must also conquer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.44,0:13:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.96,0:14:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how she always is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.93,0:14:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ranko gave up on the idea \Nof winning the match the proper way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.94,0:14:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet one thing was different this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.44,0:14:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She showed everyone her incredible will to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.94,0:15:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Her competitive spirit made Ranko neglect everyone's opinion \Nand till the final one point, show a brilliant play.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.22,0:15:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A match point is being played for Broir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa can't afford any more mistakes! \NBy all means, this service oughta be successful!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.82,0:15:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Never have I seen anyone \Nplaying there with such passion before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.32,0:16:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what top-notch players do, Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.46,0:16:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Only by doing their best there \Nthey secure themselves a later triumph.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.89,0:16:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pity that Ranko has never been \Nthe top-notch kind in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.88,0:16:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Above you, the room 28 is the mine one. \NIf you need anything, find me there. See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.94,0:16:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Was I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.84,0:16:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,never a top-notch kind too!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.82,0:16:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Forehand, huh?\NNaturally, I would've dropped the ball after it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.32,0:16:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But well, the backhand is a more reliable one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.64,0:16:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My course was firm and my aim was precise. \NBut the ball itself was lacking the momentum.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.57,0:17:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, against a fourteen-year-old\Nthis proved insufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.05,0:17:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,During the match I felt \Nlike I was facing a veteran playing tennis for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.08,0:17:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the matter now. What about your right hand? \NWhat was the doctor's diagnosis?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.58,0:17:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I should've been hitting the lobs.\NStick to the net and direct the ball down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.39,0:17:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of my usual baseline playing style.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.55,0:17:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.04,0:17:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was worth it to switch to fast serves.\NThree types.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.69,0:17:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.18,0:17:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And every time I tried to serve the curveball, \NI kept hitting the net.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.82,0:17:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Should've kept my legs straight, \Nplay the sideline tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.07,0:17:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only natural since her footwork is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.59,0:17:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still stiff while moving back and forward. \NShould've pinched her, mess her breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.94,0:17:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Backhand, backhand, backhand, forehand.\NSuch was her grand strokes' fundamental rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.83,0:17:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I first had to perturb it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.45,0:17:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa! \NYou'll see, I'll win the third round by all means!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a shame indeed, \Nbut Midorikawa lost to Broir after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.90,0:18:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, albeit tightly, \Nhas successfully cleared the second round.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.55,0:18:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, the third round, \Nthe quarter-final, begins today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.70,0:18:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! The very first match is \NMadame Butterfly vs. Marchesa Broir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.71,0:18:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, how's the situation on your side? \NIs Todo doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.01,0:18:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I, of course, \Nappreciate your concern about my right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.48,0:19:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the first time for me. \NJust gonna start it all over from zero again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.99,0:19:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike you, I'm not the type of person \Nto be afraid of starting it all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.02,0:19:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"Winning by all means" is a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.08,0:19:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's alright. \NI'm somehow sure you'll overcome even the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.47,0:19:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, \Nif you still lose after all, what then?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.72,0:19:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I never even gave it a thought. What's the point? \NIf victory depends on you only, it's secured.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.06,0:19:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Great indeed...\NHearing that is really great indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.53,0:19:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly what I hate the most \Nand also adore about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.77,0:19:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I think I'd lose for sure, \Nif I'll be relying on my right hand only.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You are much stronger after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.21,0:19:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.21,0:19:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, show your nerve, messy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.21,0:20:02.21,Default,,0,0,10,,{\an8\b0\fnVerdana}Try harder, Ms. Amateur!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.72,0:20:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheeky brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.69,0:20:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Broir say something \Nto Madame Butterfly just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.86,0:20:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is her strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.69,0:20:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She's verbally confronting Ochou \Nto piss her off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.01,0:20:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She manifests her contempt for Ochou.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.59,0:20:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.06,0:20:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Those grand strokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.03,0:20:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Broir deliberately drives the ball \Nto where Ochou will surely hit it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.48,0:20:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s like she’s assessing Ochou’s strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.96,0:20:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps she's aware of Ochou's amateur successes \Nand offers her to try to keep up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.92,0:20:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't know for sure \Nto what degree Madame Butterfly remains an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.39,0:20:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever her strength is, \Nwhile she kept being an amateur, she was incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.40,0:20:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please prove it to everyone, Madame Butterfly.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.42,0:20:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That your strength... Your techniques \Ncan compete with world rankings' #14!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.24,0:21:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Show her!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.27,0:21:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Gonna lose? I am?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.77,0:21:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And whom to?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.78,0:21:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just some 14-years-old girl.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.28,0:21:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Impossible. \NThis is simply impossible!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.30,0:21:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It can't be like that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.03,0:21:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm Ryuzaki Reika.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.50,0:21:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I let anger to take over me, \Nthis match will be my last one!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.78,0:21:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I will have to voluntarily bid my farewell to tennis.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.49,0:21:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But now's not the time for that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.65,0:22:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm not yet ready to quit tennis for good!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.83,0:23:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Aikawa Maki.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.44,0:23:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Queen's Cup quarter-finals became even hotter!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.21,0:23:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly's opponent is the one defeated Midorikawa, \Nthat girl Marchesa Broir!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.69,0:23:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,After fighting exceedingly hard, \NMadame Butterfly managed to avenge Midorikawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.86,0:23:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing less from Madame Butterfly!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.62,0:23:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But is someone else feeling not right today?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.89,0:23:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,To advance to the final and meet Hiromi there, \Nyou have to fight well, Madame Butterfly!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.50,0:24:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time: \N"It won't fly, anymore..."